rsor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">CalCOFI website<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Stations:<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Prodo stations refers to stations sampled around the same time of day (late morning) when primary productivity is measured. Cardinal stations refers to stations at a certain location to be sampled no matter what time of day. A station can be both a prodo and a cardinal station during a cruise.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Sample all Prodo stations on lines 93.3, 86.7, 83.3, and 76.7<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Sample all Prodo and Cardinal Stations on lines 80 (55.0, 70.0, 80.0, 100.0) and 90 (120.0, 90.0, 70.0, 53.0, 37.0)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Sample Station 081.8 046.9 (Santa Barabara Basin)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Depths:<\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Normally 4 depths are sampled with 6 filters total (2 DNA + 4 RNA). RNA is collected at higher volumes.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><a href=\"#\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\"> <\/span><\/a><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Exceptions:<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Less than 515 m: sample 10 m, Chl  max, and 170 m<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Less than 170 m : sample 10 m, Chl max depth<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Less than 170 m and Chl max is around 10m: sample 10 m<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Water budget:<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Ask for a duplicate bottle at 10m and chl max whenever possible<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Size Fractionation Stations: ask for 2 extra 10 m bottles and 1 extra Chl max bottle <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Please keep in mind whether the station is a DIC or Size Fractionation station. If two DIC samples are taken at one of the four depths it may be best to ask for a duplicate bottle<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><span>Do <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">NOT <\/span><span>mix water from different depth. Prioritize RNA. If short on water DNA volumes can be reduced to .5L then RNA can be reduced in 0.5L increments <\/span><\/li><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Depths:<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Normally 4 depths are sampled with 6 filters total (2 DNA + 4 RNA). RNA is collected at higher volumes.<\/div><table border><tr style = \"text-align:center;\"><td>  <\/td><td>A<\/td><td>B<\/td><td>C<\/td><td>D<\/td><td>E<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">1<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;font-weight:bold;\">Depth<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;font-weight:bold;\">DNA\/RNA<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;font-weight:bold;\">RNA Vol (L)<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;font-weight:bold;\">DNA Vol (L)<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;font-weight:bold;\">Description<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">2<\/td><t