play : table-cell;\">RNA<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">6<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\"><\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">DIC typically sampled here<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">5<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">515 m<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">RNA<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">6<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\"><\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">DIC typically sampled here<\/td><\/tr><\/table>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1043437,"guid":"BA191420040711EBB440551E52361121","previous_id":1041190,"previous_guid":"290643D0021411EBA4940B15E071F6F3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"372048C9C2E649E08AD65A0D9A809A57","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Filtration setup"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"ED383E5CA0F140E8BE568CFEF2573106","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">We use Masterflex persistaltic pumps and tubing for everything. As there are 4 RNA filters, we use a 4-channel pump head on one pump with two-stop tubing. The other pump has 2 single-channel pump heads for the 2 DNA filters. 6 L bottles are used for RNA collection and 2 L bottles are used for DNA. Bottles are wrapped in black tape to keep the seawater in the dark, but graduations are still visible on one side. Lines have 10 mL serological pipettes that have been cut to have no filter and go into the bottles and are connected to the tubing with luer connections for sterivex on the outflow. <\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/ccc9cdc27713e34b8263ddaaab92a5f9d363fe0a81cadc14cccd1d44af7508f6\/cmnp85be.png\" \/><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Notes:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Change two-stop tubing approximately halfway through the cruise (8 days)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Periodically change the 10 mL pipettes<\/li><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"A9A2BEBDC7134AFF8AB4B90FA8D813E8","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/ccc9cdc27713e34b8263ddaaab92a5f9d363fe0a81cadc14cccd1d44af7508f6\/cmnp85be.png\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1043467,"guid":"1212A5B0040D11EBB440551E52361121","previous_id":1043470,"previous_guid":"8B362700040D11EBB440551E52361121","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"0365545DA254449392BBB4EA43720CF6","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Clean up "}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"AC35D3251FC24A40AB14CA7BBCF5F58E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Flush all lines with 2L MilliQ water. When finished, open the pump heads to release pressure on the lines and turn off the pump.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Rinse all collection bottles 3x with MilliQ water. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1043470,"guid":"8B362700040D11EBB440551E52361121","previous_id":1043437,"previous_guid":"BA191420040711EBB440551E52361121","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"6F49BA5953EE4946B7C194A3EBAF9A7C","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Sample collection"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"3E14D6D8194044F3A60F1D4A070CB8EE","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">See the table above for sampling depths.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Label sterviex filters and aluminum foil for each filter with Cruise, Station, Cast, Bottle, Depth and DNA\/RNA. Keep sterivex in plastic sleeve until ready to use. Labeling example for DNA:<\/li><\/ol><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">      Sterivex: 201511 DNA        Foil: 1511 DNA<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">                       093.3 026.7                  93.27  C1<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">                       C1 B22 10 m                 B22 10 m<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/ccc9cdc27713e34b8263ddaaab92a5f9d363fe0a81cadc14cccd1d44af7508f6\/cmnn85be.png\" \/><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">3. Collect water in 2L bottles for DNA or 6L bottles for RNA. Rinse bottles with seawater 3x before collecting samples. Overfill beyond the 2L and 4L or 6L mark and bring to the lab.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">4. Prime the lines by running the extra water you collected through the lines without the filter.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">5. Pause the pump, attach filter, start the pump, and filter the sample. Start pump at 150 rpm and reduce if flow rate significantly decreases. For RNA, start a 30 minute timer and if the sample has not finished filtering at the end of 30 minutes, pause the pump and remove the filter. Measure the remaining volume with a graduated cylinder and record the volume filtered after the steps below.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">6. When filtration is done, release the line and remove the filter. The pump can be paused if all samples are done.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">7. Use a 20-50 mL syringe to purge extra water out of the filter 3x.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">8. Plug the large end of the sterivex with a luer-lock plug. Plug the small end with putty (Hemato-Seal).<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">9. Wrap the sterivex in the labeled foil, flash freeze in liquid nitrogen, and store in the dewar.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"5F85339622E64BB1B8FFDB8785A9D48E","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/ccc9cdc27713e34b8263ddaaab92a5f9d363fe0a81cadc14cccd1d44af7508f6\/cmnn85be.png\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":null,"materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>This protocol describes our sampling strategy and techniques for the <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/calcofi.org\/LRbLa\/field-work\/bottle-sampling\/ncog-project\/525-noaa-calcofi-genomics-project.html\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">NOAA-CalCOFI Ocean Genomics (NCOG) project<\/span><\/a><span>. <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">In summary, seawater for DNA and RNA from multiple depths is filtered onto Sterivex filters at each station. Although the protocol is specific to this project, it is easily adaptable for other field-based sampling.<\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1601600440}